<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>You've been added as a recipient on <%= @app_name %></title>
  <style>
    body {
      font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: #333;
      max-width: 600px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 20px;
    }
    .button {
      display: inline-block;
      background-color: #2563eb;
      color: #ffffff !important;
      text-decoration: none;
      padding: 12px 24px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-weight: 500;
      margin: 20px 0;
    }
    .warning {
      background-color: #fef3c7;
      border: 1px solid #f59e0b;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 12px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .info {
      background-color: #eff6ff;
      border: 1px solid #3b82f6;
      border-radius: 6px;
      padding: 12px;
      margin: 20px 0;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    .footer {
      margin-top: 30px;
      padding-top: 20px;
      border-top: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #6b7280;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <h1>You've been added as a recipient</h1>

  <p><strong><%= @sender.email %></strong> has added you as a recipient on <%= @app_name %>.</p>

  <div class="info">
    <strong>What is <%= @app_name %>?</strong>
    <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0;">
      <%= @app_name %> is a "dead man's switch" service. If <%= @sender.email %> stops checking in, 
      any encrypted messages they've prepared for you will be delivered automatically.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>What you need to do</h2>
  <p>
    To receive encrypted messages, you need to set up your encryption key. This involves creating 
    a secure passphrase that only you will know.
  </p>

  <p>
    <a href="<%= @invite_url %>" class="button">Set Up Your Encryption Key</a>
  </p>

  <p><small>This invite link expires in <%= @expires_in_days %> days.</small></p>

  <div class="warning">
    <strong>Important: Remember your passphrase!</strong>
    <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0;">
      Your passphrase is the only way to decrypt messages sent to you. We cannot recover it if you 
      forget it. Write it down and store it somewhere safe.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="warning">
    <strong>Security notice:</strong>
    <p style="margin: 8px 0 0 0;">
      <%= @app_name %> will never ask you for your passphrase via email or any other channel. 
      You only enter it on our secure website to decrypt messages. If you didn't expect this email 
      or don't know <%= @sender.email %>, you can safely ignore it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="footer">
    <p>This is an automated message from <%= @app_name %>. Please do not reply to this email.</p>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
